FX Rate Design doc

1. Purpose:
The objective is to fetch daily FX rates from the TIP API and compute the required monthly FX averages for partners, storing results in the table
m_lfs.lfs_ref_forex_monthly_avg_rate.
The logic must support:
• Standard partners (monthly average or N month rolling average)
• AMEX Canada (special N month, last day based averaging)
This will run once per month or daily after 10pm as we needed to create 3-4 approaches. So the leads or product need is to develop this without a service, so this has not to be run every time like a microservice does whereas it would be running daily once or monthly once.

2. TIP API Interface
Request Format
{
"inputCurrencyISOCode": "INR",
"outputCurrencyISOCode": "USD",
"date": "2026-02-13"
}

Response Format
{
"result": {
"outputCurrencyISOCode": "USD",
"outputCurrencyExchangeRate": 11,
"outputCurrencyDecimalPoint": 3
},
"request": {
"inputCurrencyISOCode": "INR",
"outputCurrencyISOCode": "USD",
"date": "2026-02-13"
}
}

FX Daily Behavior
1. TIP service returns day specific FX rate based on the requested date. 
2. Weekend and holiday dates (e.g., Fri 20, Sat 21, Sun 22) return the same FX rate because FX market is closed; TIP returns the last available business-day rate. 
3. If a requested past date exceeds 2 years, TIP returns an error. 
If TIP has no rate for a specific day, system must decide: 
• Skip the day
• Use previous business day rate
• Or treat as missing (TBD)


